  "subject": "Docs: Replace blockdiag/seqdiag with Mermaid",
  "commit_message": "Docs: Replace blockdiag/seqdiag with Mermaid\n\nReplace the abandoned sphinxcontrib-blockdiag and sphinxcontrib-seqdiag\nSphinx extensions with sphinxcontrib-mermaid. None of the documentation\nin this repository uses blockdiag or seqdiag directives; this is a\nconfig-only cleanup.\n\nThis fixes the RTD build failure caused by setuptools v82.0.0 removing\nthe bundled pkg_resources module, which sphinxcontrib-blockdiag imports\nat module level.\n\nRemove the setuptools and Pillow pins from requirements and constraints,\nas they were only needed for blockdiag/seqdiag compatibility.\n\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nChange-Id: Ib5fcef5d855629db56d189d13b2d848898fbd12b\nSigned-off-by: Matthew Watkins <mwatkins@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
